Business Brief -- York International Corp.:
   Wider Fourth-Quarter Loss
   Is Reported by Company
York, a maker of heating, ventilating, air conditioning
and refrigeration products, became a public company again in
October with a $261 million stock offering. The proceeds are
slated to retire debt taken on when the company went private
in a leveraged buy-out in 1988.
   For the full year, York reported a net loss of $4.3
million, or 18 cents a share, against net of $12.8 million,
or 64 cents a share, a year ago. Results in 1990 included an
$8.8 million extraordinary credit from a tax-loss
carry-forward of prior-year operating losses.